title: For Sale:  Femaru Fegyvar 37M
postcontent: Femaru Fegyvar 37M up for sale. Made in Hungry, supplied to the Nazis in.32apc (military issue) and in .038apc (Hungarian military) or police. Manufacturered from 1937-1944. The stamp on the trigger guard is a St Stephens Crown believed to be a non-military Hungarian mark. However barrels can be changed, so could have been switched to .32apc by the Nazis. The story behind this is that the sellers grandfather was overseas during WWII and acquired this off a German soldier along with the accompanying medal. title: For Sale:  Excalibur Exomax Crossbow for Sale!
postcontent:
For sale is an Excalibur Exomax crossbow with Varizone scope.  Like all Excalibur crossbows, this bow is incredibly accurate, so much so that you should never aim at the same spot as you just aimed at for fear of hitting the arrow you just shot!  This is no joke; these bows are that accurate!  Also, because of its design, you don’t need to take it to an archery shop to change the string if you nick it with a broadhead.  Unlike a compound crossbow where a nicked string would end your hunt and require you to take it to an archery shop to replace the string, you can simply change the string yourself in a couple of minutes and get back to your hunt.  You also do not need to carry a discharge target as these bows can be decocked, unlike a compound crossbow.
This bow will produce arrow speeds up to 350 FPS, but keep in mind that arrow speeds will vary depending on the total weight of the arrow and tip/broadhead.  That said, I have chronographed this bow at 347 FPS with a 150-grain field tip.  At 347 FPS, it has more and enough power and punch to take down the largest of North America game animals (deer, elk, bear, moose, etc.).  And, in the event you do not know, crossbows are legal archery equipment in the state of Oklahoma so long as they have a minimum of 100 pounds draw weight, are equipped with safety devices and the bolts/arrows must be a minimum of 14 inches in length.
The Exomax crossbow is one of the fastest hunting crossbows of its kind with amazing downrange performance. The Exomax comes wrapped with Realtree Xtra® camouflage and is a very comfortable bow to shoot and hunt with.

title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson
location: Boynton Beach, Palm Beach, South Florida
postcontent: Smith and Wesson model SW380 pistol without original box. This handy little backup/concealed carry gun features a 3-inch barrel, 6 shot magazine, and sights that are completely confined to the groove on the top of the pistol. These handy and accurate little .380 pistols were discontinued after S&W acquired Walther and it what decided that this pistol would compete with Walther's line of small pistols. This particular example has some light holster wear on the edges but is still in 95% condition. The pistol is very tight overall It comes with 2 extra magazines (total 3) and a strapped carrying case. This pistol has been ranged fired and has never jammed or misfired since I have owned it. It has the ability to function on any kind of ammo. I know of a LE agency that was testing 380s to figure out which to adopt. The SW 380 was the only gun that fed and fired every brand of ammo it was given.  I have another SW 380 I purchased (almost new) that has worked fine with the six or seven brands of ammo I've fed it. This pistol requires a takedown/Armorer tool to field strip which is not include, but available for about $4.00. Despite its reputation, I don't think the Sigma .380 is such a bad pistol. It's light enough and smooth enough to be easy to carry, it points well, it has a decent trigger for a pocket pistol, and mine has been boringly reliable. Changing magazines isn't easy but then you aren't likely to have one fall out by accident either. An often-maligned pistol to be sure but it seems like most of the people who denigrate the SW380 have never owned one. I don't consider this a range gun at all. More of a "carry a lot and shoot a little" pistol. Perfect for that.
